</head>

<body>

<h1>@HI{{ni}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @EM{{@HI{{ni}}}}
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{ni}}}}  indicates <a name="surface">where</a> something is "in", "at" or "on".

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{electricity^tale^notebook}}ha@KJ{{desk}}no@KJ{{above}}@EM{{ni}}arimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      The phone book is on the desk.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{ni}}}}  indicates <a name="location">where</a> something is.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{mountain^rice*field^before^life}}haima@KJ{{map^write^building}}@EM{{ni}}irasshaimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Professor Yamada is in the library now.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{ni}}}} indicates the location of an action, "in" or "at".

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{new^hear}}ha@KJ{{desk}}no@KJ{{above}}@EM{{ni}}@KJ{{placement}}itekudasai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Please put the newspaper on the desk.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{ni}}}} indicates <a name="time">time</a>.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{meeting^company}}ha9@KJ{{time}}@EM{{ni}}@KJ{{commence}}marimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Work begins at 9 o'clock.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{ni}}}} indicates movement from a larger place to a smaller place; the place may be abstract,
such as a group or society.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{gone^year^transit^environs}}sanha@KJ{{curriculum^history^study^meeting}}@EM{{ni}}@KJ{{enter}}tta.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Last year Watanabe joined a historical society.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{ni}}}} indicates <a name="direction">movement</a> towards a place.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{amerika}}@EM{{ni}}@KJ{{going}}kitai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I want to go to America.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{ni}}}} indicates the <a name="purpose">purpose</a> of an action.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{buy}}i@KJ{{thing}}@EM{{ni}}@KJ{{going}}kimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I'm going shopping.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{ni}}}} indicates the <a name="recipient">recipient</a> of an action.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{kurisumasu}}ni@KJ{{friend^accomplished}}@EM{{ni}}@KT{{purezento}}womoratta.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I received a present from my friend at Christmas.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{ni}}}} indicates the result of a change or impending change.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kono@KT{{ke-ki}}wo3tsu@EM{{ni}}@KJ{{part}}ketekudasai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Please cut this cake into 3 parts.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{ni}}}} indicates a condition that already exists.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kono@KJ{{build^thing}}no@KJ{{right^side}}ga@KJ{{teach^room}}@EM{{ni}}natteimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      The right side of this building is a classroom.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{ni}}}} marks the agent of a <a name="passive">passive</a> verb.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{electricity^car}}no@KJ{{in}}desuri@EM{{ni}}o@KJ{{gold}}wo@KJ{{take}}rareta.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      My money was taken by a pickpocket in the train.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{ni}}}} indicates the person made to do something in a <a name="causative">causative</a> sentence.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{before^life}}ha@KJ{{study^life}}@EM{{ni}}@KJ{{sino-^character}}wo@KJ{{write}}kasemashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      The teacher had the students write kanji.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{ni}}}} indicates the agent of a <a name="causative-passive">causative-passive</a> verb.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{study^life}}ha@KJ{{before^life}}@EM{{ni}}@KJ{{sino-^character}}wo@KJ{{write}}kasaremashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      The students were made to write kanji by the teacher.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{ni}}}} joins nouns (usually three or more).

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{pa-texi-}}no@KJ{{drink^thing}}ha,@KJ{{day^book^sake}}@EM{{ni}}@KT{{uisuki-}}@EM{{ni}},
      @KT{{wainn}}deshita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      The drinks available at the party were sake, whiskey and wine.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{ni}}}} indicates a pair of people of things that are often mentioned together.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{romeo}}@EM{{ni}}@KT{{jurietto}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Romeo and Juliette.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{ni}}}} indicates the basis on which an action takes place.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{ano@KJ{{reflect^brush-stroke}}ha@KJ{{possess^name}}na@KJ{{little^rumor/explanation}}@EM{{ni}}
      @KJ{{fundamentals}}duite@KJ{{make}}raremashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      That film was based on a famous novel.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
When a verb denotes a momentary action or movement, the time when it occurs may be marked by @EM{{@HI{{ni}}}}.
@EM{{@HI{{ni}}}} is used when the noun before it uses a numeral; if the noun does not use a numeral then
the particle is not used. @EM{{@HI{{ni}}}} may optionally be used with days of the week.
</p>

